org.metacsp.time.qualitative

Class SimpleAllenInterval

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.metacsp.framework.Variable
      • org.metacsp.time.qualitative.SimpleAllenInterval
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Variable>

    public class SimpleAllenInterval
extends Variable
    An implementation of the Allen interval variable. This implementation is different from AllenInterval, which is a MultiVariable representing an interval as two timepoints. This implementation is used for qualitative temporal reasoning (e.g., with the FuzzyAllenIntervalNetworkSolver), whereas the AllenInterval is used for quantitative temporal reasoning (e.g., by the AllenIntervalNetworkSolver).
    Author:
    Federico Pecora
